### Next Steps for the Team

1. **Enable in Vercel Dashboard:**
   - Go to the Vercel project dashboard
   - Click on the Analytics tab
   - Click Enable Web Analytics
   - This will activate the tracking routes (`/_vercel/insights/*`)

2. **Deploy to Vercel:**
   - Use `vercel deploy` command
   - Or connect Git repository and enable automatic deployments
   - After deployment, analytics will automatically start collecting data

3. **Monitor Analytics:**
   - After a few visitors, view data in the Analytics dashboard
   - Track page views, visitor patterns, and web vitals
   - For Pro/Enterprise plans, add custom events to track user actions

### Important Notes

- **Privacy:** The implementation respects privacy standards - see Vercel's privacy and data compliance documentation
- **No Route Support:** React implementation uses the `@vercel/analytics/react` package which offers good route tracking for SPA applications
- **Development Mode:** Analytics are collected in both development and production, but only sent to Vercel when deployed
- **Browser Compatibility:** Works with all modern browsers

